---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Learn how PeptideRundown explains peptide research, regulatory news, safety context, and editorial standards without selling peptides."
>
  <section class="bg-surface py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-text mb-6">Independent peptide education, without the sales pitch.</h1>
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none">
        <p>PeptideRundown publishes plain-language guides, research explainers, and regulatory news about peptides and related metabolic compounds.</p>
        <p>Our goal is to help readers understand what the evidence says, what remains uncertain, and where safety or legal context matters. We do not sell peptides, compounded drugs, research chemicals, or medical services.</p>
        <h2>Editorial Standards</h2>
        <p>We prioritize peer-reviewed research, regulatory sources, clinical trial records, and clearly labeled news sources. When evidence is early, animal-only, or not yet peer reviewed, we aim to say that directly.</p>
        <h2>Medical Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>PeptideRundown is educational content only. It is not medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Readers should consult a licensed healthcare professional before making health decisions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
